data.description:
You will be given a GraphQL response object representing data about GitHub repos with name containing `ramda`, sorted by stars:

```javascript
{
  "data": {
    "search": {
      "edges": [
        {
          "node": {
            "name": "ramda",
            "description": ":ram: Practical functional Javascript",
            "url": "https://github.com/ramda/ramda",
            "stargazers": {
              "totalCount": 10562
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "node": {
            "name": "ramda-fantasy",
            "description": ":ram::sparkles: Fantasy-Land compatible types for easy integration with Ramda.js",
            "url": "https://github.com/ramda/ramda-fantasy",
            "stargazers": {
              "totalCount": 982
            }
          }
        },
        // ...
      ]
    }
  }
}
```

Write a function that uses Ramda to extract sums of all stars from the response
```javascript
// for data above it would be:
10562 + 982 // 11544
```

Ramda functions to be used:
- `pipe`
- `path`
- `map`
- `sum`

The Ramda library is preloaded and accessible under `R` (e.g. `R.map`).
